author: COMSOL
description: This study simulates the thermal behavior of a computer power supply unit (PSU). Such electronic enclosures typically include cooling devices to avoid electronic components being damaged by excessively high temperatures. In this example, an extracting fan and a perforated grille cause an airflow in the enclosure to cool internal heating.
